The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro uses GCC/Clang compiler extensions: the GNU statement-expression syntax '({ ... })' and the GNU variadic comma-elision '##__VA_ARGS__'. These are documented compiler extensions, so Rule 1.2 is violated.
</scenario>
